13/03/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- EUFOR Commander Major General David Leakey and the Serb Orthodox Metropolitan of Dabar-Bosnia, Nikolay, agreed on Friday (11 March) that all alleged war criminals should be brought to justice, according to a press statement from EUFOR. 
During a meeting in Sarajevo, they also stressed that BiH should continue along the path of mutual forgiveness and reconciliation.
In other news Friday, EUFOR personnel searched the eastern Sarajevo home of former Bosnian Serb military police member Branisa Maunaga. 
According to EUFOR, the action was aimed at obtaining information on fugitives wanted by The Hague tribunal. 
Bosnian Serb police assisted in the effort. 
(RTRS, Fena, PBS BiH, NTV Hayat - 11/03/05)
